01:19.720 --> 01:21.160
David.

01:21.170 --> 01:22.510
David.

01:22.520 --> 01:23.980
- David.
- Jesus!

01:27.520 --> 01:29.160
What's the matter, David?

01:30.430 --> 01:32.150
Where's Ellen?

01:33.190 --> 01:35.030
I'm right here.

01:48.040 --> 01:49.860
Ellen!

01:56.460 --> 01:57.630
Ellen.

02:00.160 --> 02:03.180
Hey. What's wrong?

02:04.980 --> 02:07.100
I could get used to this.

02:14.930 --> 02:16.950
What are you doing with her?

02:19.900 --> 02:21.480
What do you mean?

02:23.290 --> 02:25.270
Look, I like her.

02:25.280 --> 02:29.640
L-I... she's smart, capable, but...

02:30.870 --> 02:34.820
come on... she's not
your type of lawyer.

02:35.700 --> 02:38.080
How long you going to
keep her around?

02:40.190 --> 02:45.400
Ellen brought us Katie, Katie
brought us Gregory.

02:45.900 --> 02:47.120
Right.

02:47.440 --> 02:52.070
So as long as Gregory's
still in play, so is Ellen.

02:54.670 --> 02:56.580
Simple as that.

03:05.620 --> 03:07.000
Hey.

03:07.010 --> 03:09.950
- It's Katie.
- Oh, yeah?

03:12.450 --> 03:13.540
What's the matter?

03:13.550 --> 03:15.510
Gregory Malina's dead.

03:47.250 --> 03:53.250
Damages
Season 01 Episode 10

04:11.590 --> 04:13.470
Patty was at the beach house.

04:14.320 --> 04:15.200
What did you tell her?

04:15.210 --> 04:16.380
She was there.

04:16.390 --> 04:18.480
By the time I showed up,
she was gone.

04:18.490 --> 04:20.630
Looks like she left in a hurry.

04:22.170 --> 04:25.180
Look, ellen, I want to help you.

04:26.150 --> 04:28.320
I want to get you out of here.

04:28.330 --> 04:30.780
But I don't know what
to believe anymore.

04:30.790 --> 04:32.890
Someone tried to kill me, tom.

04:35.120 --> 04:36.230
It was a
hit-and-run.

04:36.240 --> 04:38.560
Gregory malina died at the scene.

04:39.090 --> 04:40.030
1 MONTH EARLIER

04:40.040 --> 04:41.830
So we move on...

04:42.720 --> 04:44.130
to frobisher's deposition.

04:44.140 --> 04:47.900
Here's the game plan
with one major addition.

04:47.910 --> 04:49.100
Ellen.

04:49.380 --> 04:55.200
Arlington, virginia,1983,frobisher's
jaguar crashes, killing the girl he's with.

04:55.210 --> 04:58.250
Frobisher denies he was driving, but
he was drunk at the time.

04:58.260 --> 05:00.830
He's never charged, so
there's no wrongful death suit

05:00.840 --> 05:04.180
but last week, we received a tip that

05:04.190 --> 05:09.040
frobisher gave the girl's
parents stock in his company.

05:09.050 --> 05:14.620
It's hush money, so we're going to use it to
show frobisher's history of obstructing justice.

05:15.020 --> 05:20.750
If we can crack his slick facade
in the deposition and get him to
show his true colors,

05:20.760 --> 05:22.870
it'll be a victory.

05:23.760 --> 05:25.060
Thanks, everyone.

05:25.070 --> 05:26.350
Thank you.

05:28.030 --> 05:29.060
Hey, there she is.

05:29.070 --> 05:30.300
Do you really have to go, dad?

05:30.310 --> 05:31.920
Yeah, I'm afraid so.

05:31.930 --> 05:34.080
Daddy's lawyer's helping him prepare.

05:34.090 --> 05:36.690
This way he can focus better, not
be distracted by all of us.

05:36.700 --> 05:40.470
Hey, Mohammed ali used to hole
up for six weeks before a fight.

05:40.480 --> 05:41.400
Who's that?

05:41.410 --> 05:44.620
Greatest fighter of all times after me.

05:47.930 --> 05:49.950
Oh, I'm not going to have
time to do that, sweetheart.

05:49.960 --> 05:51.630
Thought you could use this.

05:54.470 --> 05:56.160
Look at you.

05:56.170 --> 05:57.660
What's that for?

05:58.610 --> 06:01.730
The night before your
stepmom and I got married,

06:02.070 --> 06:05.530
I was staying in a hotel
room nervous as shit.

06:05.540 --> 06:06.400
Dad!

06:06.410 --> 06:07.990
You're old enough.

06:08.000 --> 06:13.290
Anyway, I was cooped up, sweating
bullets and holly sent me my three iron.

06:13.300 --> 06:14.660
Why?

06:15.160 --> 06:17.190
It's your dad's good luck charm.

06:22.280 --> 06:24.560
You're my good luck charm now.

06:26.780 --> 06:27.810
What are you doing?

06:27.820 --> 06:29.690
Come on, it's just another deposition.

06:29.700 --> 06:31.860
Everything's going to be okay.

06:32.630 --> 06:35.830
We're going to be fine, trust me.

06:37.260 --> 06:39.300
How ugly is this going to get?

06:40.370 --> 06:42.500
We're reasonable people.

06:42.850 --> 06:44.360
Yes, we are.

06:45.030 --> 06:46.720
No video camera.

06:46.730 --> 06:48.690
- Unreasonable.
- Patty...

06:48.700 --> 06:50.380
What are you worried about?

06:50.390 --> 06:52.110
Your client is a matinee idol.

06:52.120 --> 06:54.900
Unless his herpes has
flared up, he'll be just fine.

06:54.910 --> 06:55.860
Nonnegotiable.

06:55.870 --> 06:58.760
- I'll give you home- court
advantage. - Not interested.

06:58.770 --> 07:01.560
But since we're on the topic...

07:02.320 --> 07:03.730
how many sessions?

07:03.740 --> 07:05.840
- Seven.
- Two.

07:05.850 --> 07:07.250
Five.

07:08.990 --> 07:10.660
I have a lot of questions.

07:10.670 --> 07:12.840
That's what wikipedia is for.

07:13.500 --> 07:16.730
Okay, three.

07:17.290 --> 07:19.610
But I get the video camera.

07:24.850 --> 07:26.520
That's a big concession.

07:26.530 --> 07:28.310
So is three days.

07:30.810 --> 07:32.310
Deal.

07:37.490 --> 07:40.410
Gregory malina's dead.

07:40.420 --> 07:42.060
Oh, my.

07:45.720 --> 07:47.650
That's horrible.

07:50.380 --> 07:53.590
I guess we'll never know
what really happened.

07:56.300 --> 07:59.730
Maybe the police will find the guy.

08:02.040 --> 08:04.090
I won't hold my breath.

08:05.080 --> 08:07.840
And, uh, ray...

08:13.050 --> 08:15.290
shame on you.

08:27.590 --> 08:30.460
What's the matter with you, ray?
You look a little green.

08:30.860 --> 08:36.320
Listen, I got it down to three
days, but she's going to have a camera.

08:37.549 --> 08:40.780
That's okay, right?
We've prepared, I'm ready.

08:41.710 --> 08:45.150
Yeah, but, art, listen...

08:45.540 --> 08:46.930
What?

08:47.710 --> 08:50.910
You're going into this
deposition exposed.

08:50.920 --> 08:51.830
How so?

08:51.840 --> 08:55.480
Well, I don't know what to do about
this arlington business, I'm sorry.

08:55.960 --> 09:01.280
She's going to attack you with it and
there's no clear way i can see to stop her.

09:02.900 --> 09:04.320
I'm not settling, ray.

09:04.330 --> 09:07.720
Well, I don't know how to protect you.

09:10.440 --> 09:13.670
I'll just have to protect
myself then, won't I?

09:15.240 --> 09:17.470
How are you going to do that?

09:25.010 --> 09:27.200
You wanted to see me?

09:28.470 --> 09:30.530
How was the beach house?

09:30.850 --> 09:34.690
Amazing. I've been meaning to thank
you all day, but it's been so busy.

09:34.700 --> 09:37.110
David and I would love to
take you and phil to dinner.

09:37.120 --> 09:39.300
Oh, forget the dinner, ellen.

09:40.230 --> 09:44.600
I've decided to take
you off the deposition.

09:44.610 --> 09:47.230
I would like you to report to felicia.

09:47.240 --> 09:50.790
She needs some work done on
a pro bono she's heading up.

09:53.010 --> 09:54.900
Vacation's over.

09:54.910 --> 09:56.960
Get back to work.

09:57.380 --> 10:00.890
Yeah, I'll do that.

10:04.040 --> 10:05.200
What are you doing?

10:05.620 --> 10:08.730
Patty's making me do all
this paralegal bullshit.

10:08.740 --> 10:10.090
For the deposition?

10:10.100 --> 10:12.920
No, it has absolutely nothing
to do with the deposition.

10:14.070 --> 10:16.310
Then put that shit away, huh

10:19.370 --> 10:21.650
Oh, wait, wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

10:21.660 --> 10:26.860
In 1983,shortly after the tragedy
of their daughter, cindy's, death,

10:26.870 --> 10:31.280
I gave the lambert family
stock in my company.

10:31.290 --> 10:32.410
Holy shit.

10:32.420 --> 10:36.270
Now, there's some people who might think
that that act was a sign of guilt...

10:36.280 --> 10:42.350
or worse, an attempt to obfuscate a crime
and to buy the lambert family's silence.

10:43.470 --> 10:48.650
To respond to that, I'm going to turn
this part over to cindy's father, carl.

10:48.660 --> 10:50.010
Thank you, arthur.

10:50.810 --> 10:55.490
Uh, folks, for my wife and I, the
particulars of this tragedy were

10:55.500 --> 10:58.390
put to rest almost three decades ago.

10:58.400 --> 11:02.300
Now this is the police
report from the accident.

11:02.310 --> 11:07.880
It documents the angle of impact and the numerous
injuries sustained by both cindy and arthur.

11:07.890 --> 11:12.390
Now, this report
convinced us at that time,

11:12.800 --> 11:17.070
and we remain convinced, that our
daughter was driving that car.

11:19.880 --> 11:21.150
Unbelievable.

11:21.160 --> 11:26.000
Arthur frobisher provided financial support
to my family because he loved my daughter.

11:26.420 --> 11:30.060
The fact that it wasn't
made public is to his credit.

11:30.070 --> 11:31.940
Character is what you do in the dark.

11:31.950 --> 11:34.460
Isn't that what christ teaches us?

11:34.470 --> 11:36.940
- Oh, jesus.
- Thank you, carl.

11:36.950 --> 11:38.810
And thank all of you for coming today.

11:38.820 --> 11:44.920
Um, I just want to say I'm relieved and grateful
that this issue can finally be put to rest.

11:48.830 --> 11:50.640
1 MONTH LATER

11:50.650 --> 11:52.930
I don't know what to believe anymore.

11:52.940 --> 11:55.070
Someone tried to kill me, tom.

11:55.080 --> 11:56.300
Come on, ellen.

11:56.310 --> 11:58.520
When I left patty's
apartment, there was a dead body.

11:58.530 --> 12:01.520
There was blood on the
floor, a window had been broken.

12:01.530 --> 12:02.530
You've got to go there.

12:02.540 --> 12:04.540
You've got to go to patty's apartment.

12:04.550 --> 12:06.130
The police didn't find anything!

12:06.140 --> 12:08.770
Then someone's covering it up!

12:08.780 --> 12:11.720
Look, without any evidence, what can I do?

12:12.520 --> 12:14.280
Let's go, parsons.

12:14.290 --> 12:17.360
Get me bail. I'll do the rest myself.

12:37.010 --> 12:38.650
Patty?

12:42.220 --> 12:44.380
Okay, boy, okay.

12:44.390 --> 12:45.740
There's a good boy.

12:45.750 --> 12:47.800
Yeah, good boy.

12:51.480 --> 12:52.820
Patty?

12:53.950 --> 12:54.950
We were set up.

12:54.960 --> 12:56.980
Or there's a leak in the office.

12:56.990 --> 13:00.180
I don't want anyone in
the deposition but you, tom.

13:00.190 --> 13:02.550
We're going into lockdown.

13:02.560 --> 13:05.000
Miss hewes, I'd like to meet
with mr. Moore and question him.

13:05.010 --> 13:06.010
No.

13:06.250 --> 13:07.790
He could be the source of the leak.

13:07.800 --> 13:10.680
This thing was buried for 25 years.

13:10.900 --> 13:12.560
I said no.

13:20.710 --> 13:23.590
Call george moore, set up a meeting.

13:25.560 --> 13:27.480
What the hell was that press conference?

13:27.490 --> 13:29.780
It was art's idea. He did it on his own.

13:29.790 --> 13:31.850
And you let him? Your job
is to control your client.

13:31.860 --> 13:33.540
He won't listen to reason.

13:33.550 --> 13:35.600
This incompetence is staggering.

13:35.610 --> 13:39.120
Listen, asshole, this
arlington fiasco's on you.

13:39.130 --> 13:41.480
I warned you from the start
this was a jackass move,

13:41.490 --> 13:44.680
and now you've exposed
yourself to patty's people.

13:44.690 --> 13:47.260
Now just lay low and let me do my job.

13:47.270 --> 13:49.210
Clearly, you can'T.

13:49.220 --> 13:52.390
Maybe I'll tell him about
you and gregory malina.

13:52.840 --> 13:53.900
You don't want to do that.

13:53.910 --> 13:56.690
You gave that kid stock and
told him when to sell it.

13:56.700 --> 14:00.110
Arthur finds out the full
story, he'll have to settle.

14:00.540 --> 14:02.430
You better be careful.

14:02.440 --> 14:05.570
- I can take you down at any moment.
- Go ahead.

14:05.580 --> 14:07.930
You'll be taking yourself down as well.

14:07.940 --> 14:10.630
You can't touch me, ray. Arthur needs me.

14:11.040 --> 14:12.550
So do you.

14:16.120 --> 14:18.570
Which one do you think looks best?

14:20.650 --> 14:21.670
I like this.

14:21.680 --> 14:23.370
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

14:23.380 --> 14:25.100
Use a windsor.

14:25.420 --> 14:27.770
It's assertive and formidable.

14:27.780 --> 14:30.260
You know, I never learned
how to tie that, actually.

14:30.770 --> 14:32.400
Can you believe that?

14:32.410 --> 14:35.230
Billionaire doesn't know
how to tie a rich man's knot?

14:35.240 --> 14:37.500
Here, sit down, I'll do it for you.

14:46.040 --> 14:48.860
- Holly usually helps me with this.
- Yeah?

14:57.810 --> 14:59.920
I want to thank you, ray.

15:02.250 --> 15:05.950
For my invaluable sartorial assistance?

15:07.340 --> 15:09.800
No, for everything.

15:10.150 --> 15:12.860
The last 16 years.

15:14.730 --> 15:18.090
Especially the last five. I
mean, I know it hasn't been easy.

15:20.660 --> 15:23.470
I know I can sometimes be kind of A...

15:25.140 --> 15:27.000
Bull in a china shop?

15:32.980 --> 15:35.980
This life is so full of people
trying to screw you, you know?

15:35.990 --> 15:39.660
You shake hands with them one day, the
next day they're trying to stab you.

15:43.670 --> 15:45.390
But you...

15:47.700 --> 15:50.780
you may be the only one I can trust, ray.

15:57.110 --> 15:59.510
You're a good friend.

16:12.440 --> 16:14.200
Hey, yeah.

16:15.070 --> 16:17.210
Let's go show 'em what we got.

16:21.420 --> 16:25.470
Spe stands for special purpose entity.

16:25.480 --> 16:29.900
I'd like to mark as exhibit
seven a chart entitled

16:29.910 --> 16:34.140
frobisher value analysis
dated march 4,2001.

16:34.150 --> 16:38.010
Do you recall seeing
this exhibit seven before?

16:38.300 --> 16:44.330
It's important to establish that it wasn't
me personally, that set up these entities.

16:45.090 --> 16:49.880
They were incorporated under the
direction of the Chief Operating Officer.

16:50.420 --> 16:56.320
So, despite running the company, you take
no responsibility for these entities that

16:56.330 --> 16:58.900
your COO created?

16:59.670 --> 17:02.260
In so far as I was his superior, yes,

17:02.270 --> 17:07.000
a certain amount of
responsibility must be inferred.

17:08.150 --> 17:10.800
But as far as direct
responsibility, no, no.

17:10.810 --> 17:14.640
I don't believe that I can be
held personally responsible.

17:15.750 --> 17:19.810
Mr. Frobisher, you were
intimately involved in

17:19.819 --> 17:23.690
founding your
company, running your company,

17:23.700 --> 17:25.470
bankrupting your company,

17:25.480 --> 17:28.140
and yet you sit here today
wanting us to believe that

17:28.150 --> 17:32.520
you have no idea where the money went.

17:32.530 --> 17:33.430
Objection.

17:33.440 --> 17:37.270
One more of those, counselor, and we're
going to have ourselves a problem.

17:37.280 --> 17:42.980
Look, all those SPEs and-and hold co's

17:42.990 --> 17:44.710
every company has them.

17:44.720 --> 17:47.580
I know when you see them up there
on a big chart with all those colors

17:47.590 --> 17:52.390
and arrows and unrestricted
this and offshore that, you...

17:53.330 --> 17:58.520
you think they've been designed
purposefully to confuse the 
heck out of you.

17:59.510 --> 18:00.290
And you know what?

18:00.300 --> 18:03.890
It works,'cause it
confuses the hell out of me,

18:03.900 --> 18:09.100
which is probably why I'm a
ceo and not a CFO or a COO.

18:10.880 --> 18:11.970
So,

18:12.430 --> 18:17.660
you don't consider it your duty
as chief executive of your company

18:18.190 --> 18:21.080
to understand its
financial underpinnings?

18:21.090 --> 18:26.030
A chief executive's job is
to set his company's agenda.

18:26.040 --> 18:28.450
You're like A... you're like a coach.

18:28.460 --> 18:32.140
Sometimes even a cheerleader.
You-you provide goals.

18:32.150 --> 18:34.820
You lead by example.

18:37.310 --> 18:44.080
I always believed that it was my duty
to inspire my employees so that...

18:44.860 --> 18:47.270
so that together we
could build something...

18:49.500 --> 18:51.270
remarkable.

19:02.720 --> 19:03.470
Hello

19:03.480 --> 19:06.680
Mr. Moore, it's Ellen Parsons.

19:07.160 --> 19:11.180
She spent the day lobbing
me softballs, loosening me up.

19:11.190 --> 19:13.140
It's going to get a lot tougher.

19:13.790 --> 19:16.620
But ray says the day went well.

19:16.630 --> 19:18.450
Good, I'm glad.

19:19.700 --> 19:21.860
Is there anything you need?

19:21.870 --> 19:25.190
Anything I can do to
make this easier for you?

19:25.200 --> 19:29.300
No, just talking to you helps.

19:29.310 --> 19:31.270
I love you, holly.

19:33.240 --> 19:35.340
I miss you guys.

19:37.060 --> 19:38.770
We miss you.

19:41.210 --> 19:44.070
- Night.
- Good night, arthur.

19:51.520 --> 19:53.630
He's going through so much.

19:54.320 --> 19:57.250
It's been hard for
you, too. Don't forget that.

19:58.900 --> 20:01.170
I'm so grateful i found you.

20:02.120 --> 20:03.870
I don't know how I would...

20:07.940 --> 20:09.780
Hey, we'll get through this.

20:10.180 --> 20:12.580
It'll be easier once you tell him.

20:14.760 --> 20:17.660
We have to wait until
after the deposition.

20:23.200 --> 20:25.390
Miss parsons.

20:42.330 --> 20:45.260
I put my ass on the line for you.

20:45.700 --> 20:46.720
Mr. Moore.

20:46.730 --> 20:51.110
I trusted you with arlington, and
your camp leaked it.

20:51.540 --> 20:53.580
Why would we do that?

20:54.740 --> 20:58.100
You don't understand how
frobisher operates, do you?

20:58.810 --> 21:03.100
Someone in your office is in his pocket.

21:03.870 --> 21:05.700
Or you are.

21:05.710 --> 21:07.270
Grow up.

21:07.280 --> 21:10.120
I could get killed for what i told you.

21:10.940 --> 21:16.300
You people had the opportunity to
take down frobisher, and you blew it.

21:16.830 --> 21:18.700
The case isn't over yet.

21:19.890 --> 21:21.820
Well, we are.

21:22.180 --> 21:24.560
You get nothing else from me.

21:27.200 --> 21:30.340
And tell tom shayes to stop calling.

21:31.800 --> 21:33.630
Mr. Moore?

21:37.430 --> 21:41.580
If there's a connection between you
and arthur frobisher, we will find it.

21:43.610 --> 21:45.570
Watch yourself.

22:12.200 --> 22:14.240
George moore is full of shit.

22:14.250 --> 22:16.500
He's saying we leaked arlington.

22:16.510 --> 22:18.240
What have you found?

22:18.250 --> 22:21.330
Moore was one of five sec
commissioners appointed.

22:21.340 --> 22:22.390
By who?

22:22.400 --> 22:23.670
The president.

22:23.680 --> 22:28.610
Moore headed up a team of investigators to
look into possible fraud in frobisher's company.

22:34.960 --> 22:36.990
Who's laura watkins?

22:37.000 --> 22:38.390
One of moore's investigators.

22:38.400 --> 22:41.900
But, in 2002,just before the
government trial, she was fired.

22:41.910 --> 22:44.130
Moore said her methods were unsound.

22:44.140 --> 22:47.120
After the trial, watkins
did this interview.

22:47.130 --> 22:51.230
She said that moore removed her
for investigating too aggressively.

22:51.240 --> 22:54.270
It was the first and last
interview she ever did.

22:54.910 --> 22:57.420
You think moore shut her down?

22:58.030 --> 23:01.020
Now she works for an accounting
firm here in the city.

23:01.980 --> 23:04.120
Have you told patty about this?

23:04.130 --> 23:05.240
No.

23:05.250 --> 23:09.310
