33:11.630 --> 33:13.480
I'm fine.

33:14.280 --> 33:16.170
Put this away.

33:18.720 --> 33:19.790
Come on.

33:22.160 --> 33:25.180
Mr. Frobisher, two days after you
returned from your trip to florida,

33:25.190 --> 33:28.470
you gave a speech to your employees.

33:30.040 --> 33:32.270
Yes, that's correct.

33:33.450 --> 33:35.180
Exhibit 67.

33:35.190 --> 33:38.510
It's a transcript of mr.
Frobisher's remarks dated...

33:38.520 --> 33:42.680
june 21,2002.

33:43.030 --> 33:47.440
Were you aware that your company was
being investigated by the sec at the time?

33:47.450 --> 33:49.280
Yes, I was.

33:49.880 --> 33:55.070
And yet you still told your employees that
the company was on sound financial ground?

33:55.080 --> 33:57.220
I was confident that we were.

33:57.230 --> 34:00.980
I firmly believed that the
sec investigation would turn up

34:00.990 --> 34:04.630
no financial irregularities whatsoever.

34:04.640 --> 34:06.280
Exhibit 68.

34:06.290 --> 34:10.730
This is an e-mail you sent
your cfo, is that correct?

34:11.989 --> 34:13.040
Yes, it is.

34:13.050 --> 34:18.400
It's a rough draft of the speech you wrote, the
one you intended to give your employees?

34:19.969 --> 34:21.510
Yes, it appears to be that.

34:21.520 --> 34:27.090
In the margin, you wrote the words, too
rosy, followed by a question mark.

34:27.480 --> 34:29.530
Too rosy.

34:30.199 --> 34:32.650
I think I was...

34:32.909 --> 34:35.389
wondering about the tone of the speech.

34:35.400 --> 34:38.429
I was debating whether or
not to acknowledge the...

34:38.870 --> 34:41.659
the climate that we were in at the time.

34:41.670 --> 34:46.739
By climate, you mean the sec was
about to expose your accounting fraud.

34:46.750 --> 34:48.870
Objection.

34:49.530 --> 34:54.230
For me to ignore the pending sec report
would have threatened my credibility,

34:54.239 --> 34:59.800
so in my final speech, I decided to
mention the investigation and even A...

35:00.450 --> 35:03.960
possible action against us by the sec.

35:03.970 --> 35:05.060
But...

35:05.070 --> 35:10.320
- you also continued to insist that your
company was financially sound?
- Yes.

35:10.330 --> 35:12.060
And your employees trusted you?

35:12.070 --> 35:13.870
Absolutely.

35:13.880 --> 35:18.620
For almost 35 years, they knew
that I was fully committed to them.

35:19.150 --> 35:22.770
There's nothing more important
to the well-being of a company

35:22.780 --> 35:27.560
than the relationshipbetween
its workers and its management.

35:32.370 --> 35:33.920
Well, that'S...

35:33.930 --> 35:36.320
sort of like a family, isn't it?

35:36.330 --> 35:39.060
Yes, it's very much like a family.

35:40.070 --> 35:43.010
And you were the head of the household?

35:43.330 --> 35:47.920
You might say you were both husband
and father to your employees.

35:47.930 --> 35:49.750
Objection.

35:54.440 --> 35:56.780
You could say that, yes.

35:58.060 --> 36:01.420
And was it your job to
hold the family together?

36:05.160 --> 36:06.820
Yes, it was.

36:07.100 --> 36:09.030
- And you failed.
- Objection.

36:09.040 --> 36:10.570
I'll rephrase.

36:12.990 --> 36:15.210
I mean... was it...

36:15.720 --> 36:18.710
- very painful for you when you failed?
- Objection.

36:18.720 --> 36:21.500
- I'm warning you, counselor.
- I'm merely asking mr. Frobisher

36:21.510 --> 36:23.840
about his commitment to his company.

36:23.850 --> 36:28.420
Would you agree that the crumbling
of that relationship is nothing less,

36:28.430 --> 36:31.590
really, than the
dissolution of a marriage?

36:33.520 --> 36:35.810
You watch what you say.

36:36.950 --> 36:38.850
Your position...

36:38.860 --> 36:43.550
is that the collapse of your company
wasn't your fault, is that right?

36:43.560 --> 36:45.630
Yes, that's correct.

36:46.260 --> 36:49.030
I was misled by the accountants.

36:49.040 --> 36:52.380
Um, I take full responsibility
but not the blame.

36:52.390 --> 36:54.920
Well, I understand...
it's like marriages.

36:54.930 --> 36:57.510
Companies just fail sometime.

36:57.520 --> 36:59.240
Irreconcilable differences.

36:59.250 --> 37:01.640
No one is to blame.
Is that your position?

37:01.650 --> 37:03.720
One more like that, and we will walk out.

37:03.730 --> 37:07.130
Is that your position, mr. Frobisher?

37:07.140 --> 37:11.700
- Or is the failure of this relationship,
as you call it, your failure?
- Patty...

37:11.710 --> 37:13.880
- patty, I'm warning you.
- Your breach of trust,

37:13.890 --> 37:15.120
- your infidelity...
- You are out of line...

37:15.130 --> 37:16.810
Goddamn it!

37:17.870 --> 37:20.020
This is bullshit!

37:20.030 --> 37:21.750
- This is bullshit!
- Art...

37:21.760 --> 37:23.660
I'm done here. This is bullshit.

37:23.670 --> 37:25.830
This is absolute
bullshit, and you know it.

37:25.840 --> 37:27.300
No, I'm done. Uh-uh.

37:27.310 --> 37:28.730
- No, I'm done.
- Arthur...

37:28.740 --> 37:31.090
I'll see you in court, you bitch.

37:46.550 --> 37:49.690
Are you kidding me? Divorce?

37:49.700 --> 37:51.560
You blindsided me,
you know that, Holly?

37:51.570 --> 37:52.920
We'll talk about this later, Arthur.

37:52.930 --> 37:55.810
Did you want patty hewes
to use this against me?

37:55.820 --> 37:56.880
- Of course not.
- Is that what you wanted?

37:56.890 --> 37:58.210
- Of course not.
- Then why now?

37:58.220 --> 37:59.180
Why now, holly?

37:59.190 --> 38:01.680
- Arthur, this isn't about the case,
it's about us.
- Bullshit! No, bullshit!

38:01.690 --> 38:02.910
You screwed me!

38:02.920 --> 38:04.690
You screwed yourself, too,
you know that?

38:04.700 --> 38:07.830
This is our money. We're
talking about our money here.

38:08.110 --> 38:09.940
- I'm sorry, arthur.
- Look at this.

38:09.950 --> 38:11.890
- I gave you everything you ever wanted!
- Stay away from me.

38:11.900 --> 38:13.160
Stay away from me.

38:13.170 --> 38:15.150
I could've ended this
anytime I wanted, you know.

38:15.160 --> 38:17.710
I could've made this go away months ago.

38:17.860 --> 38:19.710
- Hey, what are you do... Come on.
- Move the car.

38:23.130 --> 38:25.600
Did you even think about the
kids? You ever think about that?

38:25.610 --> 38:28.540
You move that car, I will kill you.

38:29.760 --> 38:31.850
Open the window; let's talk. Come on.

38:31.860 --> 38:34.410
Holly, come on, open the window...

38:34.770 --> 38:36.130
Open the...

38:40.400 --> 38:45.130
holly, talk to me, will ya?

38:45.140 --> 38:46.720
Stop the car!

38:46.730 --> 38:48.570
Stop the damn car!

39:09.780 --> 39:12.900
Hey, ray. The hell with this.

39:13.750 --> 39:17.440
I can't take any more of
it. Just make an offer.

39:22.230 --> 39:24.650
How's my favorite divorce attorney?

39:24.660 --> 39:26.970
Men and women still hate
each other, so I'm good.

39:30.160 --> 39:32.490
Oh, boy, thanks for the tip.

39:32.940 --> 39:35.670
I hope it didn't get you
in trouble with your client.

39:36.840 --> 39:39.220
I just blamed it on
the clerks at the court.

39:39.730 --> 39:41.970
High-profile divorce like this...

39:41.980 --> 39:44.850
Yeah, they would have leaked
it to the press anyway.

39:46.750 --> 39:50.150
Besides, this thing's going
to be about custody...

39:50.160 --> 39:52.080
and infidelity.

39:53.650 --> 39:55.200
I owe you one.

39:57.300 --> 39:59.120
Where they serve tequila.

39:59.890 --> 40:01.060
Very nice.

40:01.070 --> 40:02.750
Ellen, where are you
going to work now?

40:02.760 --> 40:05.430
I don't know. I have
no idea! I don't care.

40:05.440 --> 40:06.940
Do you know where I can
work? Where can I work?

40:06.950 --> 40:09.730
New york city subway. The
new york city subway station.

40:15.430 --> 40:17.010
You could a sushi photographer.

40:25.070 --> 40:26.370
Raymond.

40:27.010 --> 40:29.740
- 500
- 500?

